Subject:	Joint QSE project managers / WMS meeting

There have been several requests from market participants for a forum to
be used to communicate issues on current market operations and upcoming
changes on a more formal basis.  In response to this request, ERCOT is
renewing the QSE project manager meetings which were used prior to the
opening of the ERCOT market to address wholesale market issues.  The
first meeting will be conducted jointly with the ERCOT wholesale market
subcommittee meeting on Tuesday, November 13th 2001. Tentative agenda
items for the first meeting are as follows:

*	9:30 - 9:45	Introductions and review of agenda
*	9:45 - 10:00 Future QSE project Manager Meetings
*	10:00 - 11:30 Market Operations - Balancing Instructions
Involving Operational Congestion and Interim Resource Specific
Deployment Instructions
*	11:30 - 12:30 Lunch
*	12:30 - 1:00 Settlements - Mismatched Schedules
*	1:00 - 1:30 ERCOT Phase II systems progress update
*	1:30 - 3:30 WMS meeting

If you are planning to attend, please RSVP with Terry Waggoner at
twaggoner@ercot.com no later than Friday November 9th, 2001.  If you
have any questions, you may contact me at the number below of call your
assigned ERCOT client representative.

